Ross Patterson, Jarred Taylor, Dan Hollaway, and Jessie Wiseman discuss the Donald Trump impeachment inquiry and what it means for Democrats in 2020, the Swedish 16 year old Greta Thunberg who was just nominated for a Nobel Prize for her climate change speech, San Francisco residents putting boulders in the streets in front of their houses to stop homeless people from sleeping there, the Police Tesla that ran out of battery life during a pursuit, and the Indiana woman who adopted a 6 year old that turned out to be a 22 year old dwarf.
